<DOC><DOCNO> AP880706-0054 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-06-88 0302EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Bangladesh-Hurricane     07-06 0100</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Bangladesh-Hurricane,0105</SECOND><HEAD>Storm Kills 6, Injures 200</HEAD><DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A hurricane swept over northwesternBangladesh, killing six people, injuring about 200 and batteringvillages, police said today.   The storm hit villages in the Bogra district, 100 milesnorthwest of Dhaka, on Tuesday night, police said.   Abdur Rahman Khan, a local government official, said thehurricane and four days of heavy rain that preceded it hadextensively damaged rice crops.   More than 90 people have died in floods and storms in Bangladeshsince the monsoon season started in April.   Last year, the monsoons claimed more than 1,200 lives.</TEXT></DOC>